# Go — error handling

- Always check errors explicitly with `if err != nil { return ..., err }`.
- Never use `panic` in request-handling or business logic paths. `panic` is only acceptable in `main()` for unrecoverable startup failures.
- Wrap errors with context using `fmt.Errorf("operation: %w", err)` so callers can inspect the chain.
- Do not silently discard errors with `_`.
- Return `error` as the last return value; never use a bool to signal failure when an error gives more information.
